WEBVTT

00:02.978 --> 00:29.970
We're still in Mark chapter four and we've got two more weeks here as we're examining how God grows our faith.

00:30.146 --> 00:33.952
Mark 4 verse 26, this time I wanted to read it from the NIV version.

00:34.032 --> 00:35.334
It says it a little bit differently.

00:35.815 --> 00:48.073
It says, and he said unto them, the kingdom of God is as if a man should sow seed on the ground and should sleep by night and rise by day.

00:49.315 --> 00:51.218
And the seed should sprout and grow.

00:51.258 --> 00:53.842
He himself does not know

00:54.306 --> 00:54.807
How?

00:55.207 --> 00:56.449
Is that the NIV?

00:56.770 --> 00:59.474
The kingdom of God is like a man scatters seed on the ground.

00:59.494 --> 01:03.800
Yeah, I thought that it says scatters because I think the new King James says so.

01:04.822 --> 01:06.424
So I'm just going to read from the NIV.

01:07.305 --> 01:09.208
This is what the kingdom of God is like, he says.

01:09.248 --> 01:15.518
It's as if a man scatters seeds on the ground night and day whether he sleeps or gets up.

01:17.060 --> 01:18.382
Sometimes it doesn't matter what you do.

01:19.584 --> 01:20.465
God is bigger.

01:20.525 --> 01:22.889
Doesn't matter what you do.

01:22.909 --> 01:23.890
God is working.

01:24.322 --> 01:31.069
whether he sleeps or wakes up, whether he's working hard or resting, whether he's putting the effort and the time in or not.

01:32.210 --> 01:47.466
Man, I just kind of like that, no matter what we are doing, if we will plant the seed in the ground, that the seed will sprout and grow, though he doesn't know how.

01:48.888 --> 01:50.930
So even without our knowledge,

01:51.362 --> 01:56.768
Sometimes without our input, without our knowledge, amazingly, God can do things.

01:56.788 --> 01:57.609
Isn't that incredible?

01:59.751 --> 02:01.833
The old saying, God helps those who help themselves.

02:02.034 --> 02:02.654
That's not true.

02:04.456 --> 02:05.057
It's alive.

02:06.418 --> 02:07.980
I'm not saying he shouldn't help yourself.

02:08.040 --> 02:11.344
Some of you guys could do some things to help yourself, and there's nothing, nothing wrong with that.

02:12.144 --> 02:13.446
But don't throw God into that.

02:13.726 --> 02:15.268
That's just you helping yourself.

02:15.408 --> 02:16.509
That's you being wise.

02:16.809 --> 02:19.092
Scripture says, if you're wise, you are wise for yourself.

02:19.973 --> 02:21.074
That's what Proverbs says.

02:21.474 --> 02:21.775
Right?

02:21.975 --> 02:23.719
So that's a good thing.

02:23.759 --> 02:24.861
It's not a negative thing.

02:25.923 --> 02:26.825
You can help yourself.

02:26.925 --> 02:28.208
You can help yourself out a lot.

02:28.248 --> 02:32.196
You can go through a lot less pain if you would learn some wisdom.

02:33.058 --> 02:42.898
However, even without wisdom, even just the dumb sheep, come on somebody, anybody ready to associate with a lack of wisdom?

02:43.042 --> 02:45.646
Man, oh gosh, how many mistakes have I made?

02:45.706 --> 02:49.571
How many steps should I have taken that I didn't take?

02:49.611 --> 02:52.274
How many steps should I not have taken that I did?

02:53.035 --> 02:54.718
My goodness, yeah, I mean, that's my yes.

02:54.938 --> 02:59.745
But you know, my goodness, God doesn't just help those who help themselves.

03:00.125 --> 03:07.735
Truth is, night or day, whether he sleeps or gets up, the seed that I have sewn into the kingdom of God keeps working.

03:08.356 --> 03:12.722
What I have placed in his hand, what I have placed in his care,

03:12.962 --> 03:14.585
He keeps working.

03:14.986 --> 03:29.711
Even when I don't know what to do, even when I make mistakes and I don't do what I should do, whether I sleep or whether I wake, whether I'm working, whether I'm not working, whether I'm resting, there's this principle that God causes growth.

03:30.853 --> 03:32.496
God causes growth.

03:32.596 --> 03:33.778
I don't cause growth.

03:34.338 --> 03:41.128
But I release what I have, I plant it into the soil, and this is what the kingdom of God is like.

03:41.188 --> 03:43.472
It's not you figuring things out.

03:44.093 --> 03:45.455
It's not you getting better.

03:45.916 --> 03:47.137
It's not you getting bigger.

03:47.217 --> 03:48.199
It's God is bigger.

03:48.239 --> 03:54.729
It's a realization that what I have committed unto him, he is faithful to bring that to fruition.

03:54.809 --> 03:57.072
He is faithful to bring that thing to pass.

03:57.112 --> 04:01.179
And so whether the man sleeps or wakes up, this is what's happening.

04:01.279 --> 04:01.980
It's growing.

04:02.260 --> 04:03.442
He doesn't even know how.

04:03.874 --> 04:06.537
How does it grow all by itself?

04:07.298 --> 04:09.500
The soil produces grain.

04:09.540 --> 04:12.283
And now it starts going through the process of production.

04:12.404 --> 04:16.628
First, the stalk, then the head, then the full kernel within the head.

04:17.009 --> 04:21.354
As soon as the grain is ripe, he puts the sickle in because the harvest has come.

04:22.134 --> 04:25.238
And so we've been examining how God grows our faith.

04:25.258 --> 04:28.882
We've been examining how God causes growth.

04:28.962 --> 04:31.785
And so I want to look today at another principle.

04:32.045 --> 04:34.487
We've been looking at organic life principles.

04:35.068 --> 04:36.649
These are true of all living things.

04:36.669 --> 04:39.011
Do we have any living things in here today?

04:39.031 --> 04:39.312
A few.

04:39.452 --> 04:40.153
Okay, cool.

04:40.173 --> 04:43.436
So this is true of you that you are growing.

04:43.776 --> 04:45.037
This is true living things.

04:45.057 --> 04:46.458
Those are things that God has made.

04:47.019 --> 04:47.880
Mechanical things.

04:47.900 --> 04:49.521
Those are things that humans have made, right?

04:49.902 --> 04:55.487
And so so many times we get a mechanical mindset when really we need to, we need to have more of a natural mindset.

04:55.507 --> 04:56.508
How does God do things?

04:56.548 --> 04:58.770
Well, God does things with

04:58.882 --> 04:59.883
This is our word for today.

05:00.244 --> 05:01.506
Sustainability.

05:02.647 --> 05:04.109
Sustainability.

05:04.830 --> 05:09.056
God, everything God does, He does with sustainability.

05:09.857 --> 05:15.946
All of nature, if you look around nature, nature is by itself sustainable.

05:17.187 --> 05:18.749
It will sustain itself.

05:19.130 --> 05:27.922
Sustainability, the definition for sustainability is that a living thing will be able to maintain or sustain.

05:28.258 --> 05:30.562
quality of life over a long period of time.

05:30.822 --> 05:32.124
That's what sustainability means.

05:33.246 --> 05:40.838
And God, when he plants something, when he grows something, when he creates something, he does it with sustainability.

05:41.740 --> 05:52.397
So that means, what that means is that when you and I are planted, when our faith is planted, by God, sustainability will be part of that process.

05:52.457 --> 05:55.602
Now, right off the bat, I have to point out that sustainability

05:55.810 --> 06:22.482
was treat the word was invented back in the seventeen hundreds by a german guy he was trying to talk about ways of farming and particularly ways of i think it's called smelting smelting uh... uh... they were smelting smelting silvers what they were doing and he wrote he wrote a book about how they should use sustainable practices and smelting silver nowadays though three hundred years later it's kind of

06:22.562 --> 06:24.408
It's become a buzzword.

06:24.428 --> 06:26.234
It's a real popular word now.

06:26.615 --> 06:27.959
And it's really kind of been hijacked.

06:27.980 --> 06:34.962
And it's more of a political term for a type of environmental policy.

06:35.746 --> 06:41.715
So when I talk about sustainability, whatever side you fall of that political spectrum, I really don't mind.

06:42.115 --> 06:44.839
You go do some research, vote your conscience, that's great.

06:45.240 --> 06:47.022
I'm not talking about that.

06:48.424 --> 06:53.372
So a lot of times, sustainability feels like you watch YouTube videos on it, which I did some research this week.

06:53.432 --> 07:03.186
It feels kind of like they're saying, well, humans should have a lesser quality of life so that we can take care of nature and that nature, we have to sacrifice for nature.

07:03.426 --> 07:08.536
And if that's your view of sustainability, you'll actually get a weird view of the rest of this message, okay?

07:08.556 --> 07:10.480
That's not what I'm talking about.

07:10.560 --> 07:18.254
When God creates things with sustainability, he doesn't mean, look, you have to sacrifice that somebody else can thrive, right?

07:18.274 --> 07:20.940
You have to suffer so that somebody else can do well.

07:21.000 --> 07:24.306
That's not God's version of sustainability.

07:24.930 --> 07:26.132
Now you can sacrifice.

07:26.212 --> 07:27.734
That's a part of his version.

07:27.794 --> 07:31.438
But anyway, so I just I just want you to just reset for just a minute.

07:31.458 --> 07:41.451
Just take what you've heard about sustainability and Nike making sustainably resource shoes and you know, like just just take all that and like that's a whole nother discussion.

07:41.531 --> 07:44.195
You can watch some YouTube videos on that if you want.

07:44.855 --> 07:48.961
I'm talking about the way in which nature is self-sustaining.

07:49.902 --> 07:53.106
The way in which a forest, if you leave it, for instance,

07:53.506 --> 07:56.490
for a hundred years, it'll still be there when you come back.

07:57.011 --> 08:05.984
A hundred years later, a thousand years later, that forest, and actually some of those trees will still be there a thousand years later.

08:07.426 --> 08:15.157
So when I say sustainability, I don't mean like Nike trying to offset some of the carbon footprint of their shoe production, right?

08:15.518 --> 08:21.106
I'm talking about actually the way in which things, God created things to sustain themselves.

08:21.442 --> 08:23.446
to maintain a quality of life.

08:24.247 --> 08:29.176
Basically, he never assigns a quality of life that he doesn't expect the living thing to maintain.

08:32.161 --> 08:33.684
So he doesn't do that.

08:33.964 --> 08:38.232
Now, in America, we're really bad at sustainability.

08:38.653 --> 08:46.226
We prefer short bursts of energy, short bursts of effectiveness and production.

08:46.562 --> 08:50.171
And we knock it out between eight and five or whatever it might be.

08:50.211 --> 08:54.823
We hit it hard, we grind hard, but it's not sustainable.

08:55.665 --> 09:00.657
And we don't even plan on it to be sustainable because sustainability is not even in our mindset.

09:00.697 --> 09:02.963
And so you'll ask people, how do you plan on keeping this up?

09:02.983 --> 09:04.306
And they'll be like, I don't know.

09:04.546 --> 09:06.749
But I'm just going to ride it as long as I can.

09:06.789 --> 09:11.775
And so the idea of sustainability is a natural concept.

09:11.835 --> 09:14.498
It's not necessarily a mechanical concept.

09:14.979 --> 09:18.463
Machines, for instance, work really hard for a short period of time.

09:19.404 --> 09:20.745
And then they die.

09:21.386 --> 09:22.428
And then you get a new one.

09:23.449 --> 09:26.092
Your iPhone works really hard for a short period of time.

09:26.112 --> 09:29.856
And then they change the settings on an update.

09:29.876 --> 09:31.438
And that crashes your phone.

09:32.239 --> 09:34.482
And so that you have to go buy a new one.

09:34.626 --> 09:35.888
because it's not good for business.

09:36.068 --> 09:38.472
Sustainability is not really that good for business.

09:39.233 --> 09:49.810
If you had Everlasting Gobstopper, it wouldn't be good for business, which is why Willy Wonka wasn't allowed to make Everlasting Gobstopper, because we want people to buy new gum.

09:49.830 --> 09:51.352
We want people to buy new stuff.

09:51.753 --> 10:02.770
But in God's nature, God created things to be sustainable, which means as God is building you and as God is building your faith, he wants your faith to be sustainable.

10:02.946 --> 10:07.988
I was talking to somebody recently about one of the sermons that I was preaching on.

10:08.008 --> 10:09.435
I think it was energy transfer.

10:09.676 --> 10:11.986
And I was talking about that we are producers.

10:12.034 --> 10:14.237
And I kind of ended the sermon with saying, what are you producing?

10:14.257 --> 10:15.479
What are you producing in your home?

10:15.499 --> 10:16.601
What are you producing in your life?

10:16.621 --> 10:18.524
What are you producing in your relationship with God?

10:18.704 --> 10:19.986
What are you producing with your money?

10:20.607 --> 10:24.373
And so I just began just asking, go home and pray about this.

10:24.913 --> 10:28.239
And I was talking to this person and they were like, man, I really need to be producing a lot more.

10:28.319 --> 10:29.961
I really need to start producing a lot more.

10:30.402 --> 10:31.423
And I said, well, that's great.

10:31.503 --> 10:33.386
My next sermon is on sustainability.

10:35.069 --> 10:41.138
Because if you simply take the idea of a producer and the way that America thinks of production,

10:41.538 --> 10:42.119
You will.

10:42.179 --> 10:43.221
You'll work really hard.

10:43.241 --> 10:52.655
You'll see all the ways in which you fall short and you'll be like, this is a long list and you'll start attacking the list and yet man seeds don't have to do lists.

10:55.018 --> 11:00.346
They don't, they don't, they don't have a to do list with deadlines and due dates.

11:00.407 --> 11:08.018
Now I know in our, in our job and our work environments, we do and there's nothing necessarily wrong with that, but I'm saying you can't transfer that onto your faith.

11:08.674 --> 11:12.298
Okay, that's the American way, that's not God's way.

11:12.318 --> 11:15.041
The way that God works, God works through sustainability.

11:15.081 --> 11:19.606
In other words, He never asks you to do something that you cannot keep doing for a long period of time.

11:20.968 --> 11:27.976
And so many of us, our relationship with God, our Christian faith is like this and then like this and kind of like the American banking system.

11:28.336 --> 11:30.779
It's like this and then like, oh, there goes SVB.

11:30.799 --> 11:32.320
And then I was like, oh, there goes signature.

11:33.542 --> 11:33.782
Why?

11:33.822 --> 11:37.266
Because they're not sustainable.

11:37.666 --> 11:42.873
And so you can apply this to finances, you can apply this to relationships, you can apply this to your Christian walk.

11:43.174 --> 11:48.521
But the truth is no matter what you're doing, when God is in it, it is sustainable.

11:49.502 --> 11:55.391
He'll never ask you to start something that you cannot continue at the same quality for a long period of time.

11:55.651 --> 11:58.935
And so I want you guys to grow in your faith in a sustainable way.

11:59.256 --> 12:06.546
Not in a, oh my goodness, I need to work really hard over the next three weeks to check off all the lists and start all the stuff and do all the things.

12:07.394 --> 12:08.435
for a short period of time.

12:09.436 --> 12:10.818
That won't help you grow.

12:10.858 --> 12:15.583
It'll help you produce some good things, but then you'll lose the production.

12:16.204 --> 12:20.469
It'll help you achieve some good things, but that achievement won't last.

12:20.809 --> 12:32.022
And so what God wants for you is a sustainable walk, a sustainable faith, a faith that you can start right now, that you can start walking forward, and you can continue.

12:32.322 --> 12:35.666
Basically, instead of short bursts, we're talking long obedience.

12:36.610 --> 12:37.632
in the same direction.

12:38.473 --> 12:44.704
Instead of short bursts of dedication, you're better off having long obedience in the same direction.

12:47.850 --> 12:51.376
And this is not a lazy way to do things.

12:51.396 --> 12:55.764
All right, this is not, this is not to say, well, just whatever you feel like doing tomorrow, go ahead and do it.

12:55.784 --> 12:58.048
No, like trees aren't lazy.

12:58.528 --> 12:59.410
They're working.

13:00.354 --> 13:05.460
They're striving, but they're not striving to fulfill a checklist.

13:05.480 --> 13:08.283
They're not striving to reach a deadline.

13:09.024 --> 13:14.731
They're not striving with an exterior burden of list, of goals.

13:15.291 --> 13:22.560
They're striving to transfer the energy of what's in front of them, to allow it to work within them and allow that to produce something from them.

13:22.600 --> 13:28.146
They have no, like an apple tree doesn't have a set quota of how many apples they need to produce this season.

13:28.930 --> 13:30.112
If they produce one, cool.

13:30.132 --> 13:31.293
If they produce 100, cool.

13:31.954 --> 13:33.396
They're just here to produce apples.

13:34.498 --> 13:35.920
And the same is true with church.

13:35.940 --> 13:39.745
There's no good church size or bad church size.

13:40.406 --> 13:43.690
So God's not simply looking for churches that are gathering a lot of people.

13:43.730 --> 13:48.417
There are smaller churches that are also being obedient to God, that are gathering a few people.

13:48.897 --> 13:55.186
Now, if you're not gathering any people, then you should probably shut your doors down and stop being a church because you're literally not producing fruit.

13:55.522 --> 14:01.007
But the rate of fruit, this is where we put so much pressure on ourselves.

14:02.229 --> 14:05.612
And it's simply, it's not sustainable.

14:06.373 --> 14:13.360
I was talking to somebody this week who's graduating high school and starting life.

14:13.840 --> 14:16.042
And so they have a list of things they should do, right?

14:16.322 --> 14:17.904
Get a job, get a car.

14:18.605 --> 14:24.050
And the truth is, American culture will be happy to give you that list.

14:24.706 --> 14:26.073
You don't even have to think.

14:27.218 --> 14:31.218
So in many ways it's actually easier to stay on

14:31.426 --> 14:54.834
the the wheel to push and to work and to have these short bursts because because everybody else is doing every movie that you watch every sitcom that you watch every game show they're all talking about the same thing right so if you're I don't know if you're if you're an 18 year old female just graduated high school okay this is what you need to do you need to you need to get a job you need to get a car to get back and forth to that job you need to go to college so that you can get a better job

14:55.618 --> 14:56.719
All right, those are the three things.

