15:07.829 --> 15:08.349
Okay, cool.

15:08.569 --> 15:09.930
Then all of a sudden you get those things.

15:09.970 --> 15:12.933
And then after a while you figure out that the boy you got wasn't so great.

15:12.953 --> 15:14.214
So you need to get a better one.

15:14.234 --> 15:15.936
So you go shopping for a better one.

15:16.396 --> 15:18.378
Your car breaks down because that wasn't so great.

15:18.398 --> 15:20.199
But by now you have more money from your job.

15:20.219 --> 15:21.060
You can get a better one.

15:21.300 --> 15:25.604
But then you got to go to school to get a better job so that you can get a better car and upgrade your life and

15:25.584 --> 15:30.608
Constantly, you're just, you wind up, you're 40 years old and you're sitting back, what have I done?

15:30.628 --> 15:31.249
Where am I going?

15:32.750 --> 15:34.572
You're saying in the same boat with everybody else.

15:34.732 --> 15:37.815
We're all just going down this track and we don't have to think about it.

15:38.135 --> 15:39.997
We don't have to work at it.

15:40.017 --> 15:41.638
We just, we just, we just chug along.

15:43.139 --> 15:46.883
And yet God has a different way of doing things.

15:46.903 --> 15:55.090
God, there's a lack of management that is actually more productive than the over management.

15:56.642 --> 15:59.607
For instance, a tree doesn't have this set path.

16:00.027 --> 16:03.492
He's not looking around at other trees trying to figure out what he should do.

16:04.995 --> 16:09.201
He's receiving from what is above him, the power above him, he's receiving from God.

16:10.263 --> 16:12.666
I'm calling it a he, that's not right, but whatever.

16:13.127 --> 16:15.771
It is receiving, let's get those pronouns right.

16:16.292 --> 16:25.586
It's receiving from God, and it's converting carbons, photosynthesizing, and creating, and it's growing where it is with what it has.

16:25.954 --> 16:29.599
And it's, and it's simply this long obedience thing.

16:30.981 --> 16:36.770
And what's amazing is when, when, when, because it's actually kind of harder when you're 18 and people say, well, what are you going to do with your life?

16:36.790 --> 16:37.471
And you say, I don't know.

16:39.333 --> 16:40.455
Cause that's not acceptable.

16:41.797 --> 16:42.618
Oh, you're not married yet.

16:42.758 --> 16:43.339
You're 27.

16:43.679 --> 16:44.380
You're not married yet.

16:44.801 --> 16:44.981
Why?

16:45.021 --> 16:46.163
Because that's not on the track.

16:46.804 --> 16:51.090
But, but when you're actually following God's will for your life, you're, you're not as

