54:24.579 --> 54:25.941
Those that hunger for it, get it.

54:26.341 --> 54:27.863
Those that desire for it, get it.

54:28.083 --> 54:29.164
So Lord, make me hungry.

54:29.765 --> 54:31.167
And I don't know.

54:31.187 --> 54:32.909
Sometimes you don't feel like coming to church.

54:34.871 --> 54:36.953
Sometimes I don't feel like coming to church, right?

54:37.914 --> 54:41.458
And it's like, okay, on those days, Lord, make me hungry.

54:42.722 --> 54:44.184
for your presence, make me hungry.

54:44.484 --> 54:47.028
Because sometimes we'll be like, well, I'm just gonna do it anyway by golly.

54:47.349 --> 54:48.871
And it's like, you just, you just do it.

54:52.095 --> 54:52.836
You just do it.

54:53.497 --> 54:55.460
Well, you lose the rewards of it.

54:56.361 --> 54:57.403
You miss out.

54:57.964 --> 54:59.706
Say, God, okay, I'm going to do it.

55:00.147 --> 55:01.008
But Lord, make me hungry.

55:01.228 --> 55:02.530
Same is true in our marriages.

55:04.072 --> 55:05.234
It's like, it's like, okay, fine.

55:05.254 --> 55:06.816
There's this list of things she wants me to do.

55:06.916 --> 55:07.357
Lovely.

55:07.778 --> 55:08.318
I'll try.

55:08.358 --> 55:10.962
But Lord,

55:11.682 --> 55:21.715
Lord, make me desiring for her and not just for her, but for her, for her benefit, for her blessing, for her growth.

55:22.476 --> 55:29.446
Make me desiring because until I want it, I'm just doing it and that's not sustainable.

55:30.407 --> 55:33.631
Sustainable is what I would desire because that's what I'll return to.

55:33.952 --> 55:36.014
That's what I'll slip into when things get hectic.

55:36.034 --> 55:37.476
That's what I'll shift back to.

55:37.657 --> 55:38.738
That's my fall back.

55:39.842 --> 55:43.226
My desire, so God changed my desire.

55:43.246 --> 55:45.048
If you don't desire Him, ask Him to change.

55:45.228 --> 55:47.731
If you don't desire what is right, ask Him to change your desire.

55:49.814 --> 55:53.318
So that we're not Danita or Paisley, Danada.

55:54.078 --> 56:03.590
Father, in Jesus name, Lord, we pray that you would change, change our desires, change our hearts, or make us sustainable.

56:04.931 --> 56:07.474
Help us, your kingdom is sustainable.

56:09.634 --> 56:11.676
And yet we mess it up when we try to pave it.

56:13.378 --> 56:15.980
And when we try to steal the product from it.

56:19.604 --> 56:23.668
Instead, Lord, let us, let us enjoy the complexity of it.

56:25.690 --> 56:30.414
Even the parts that don't make sense to us because your kingdom grows, whether we know how it did it or not.

56:31.656 --> 56:33.798
So let us enjoy the complexity of your word.

56:33.818 --> 56:35.760
Let us enjoy the complexity of prayer.

56:35.820 --> 56:38.162
Let us enjoy the complexity of care groups.

56:38.914 --> 56:48.809
the complexity of city chapel, not be inconvenienced by it, but let us enjoy, let us value the complexity of it.

56:50.772 --> 56:52.755
That you're pulling all kinds of things together.

56:52.775 --> 56:54.237
You're doing all kinds of things.

56:54.397 --> 56:55.659
We see it.

56:55.679 --> 56:57.942
We don't even know how all things work together.

56:57.962 --> 57:01.187
We don't know how they all work together, but we believe your word says they all work together.

57:01.227 --> 57:08.498
So Lord, may we not rush to pave things and flatten things and organize things so much that we lose

57:08.610 --> 57:09.531
the life out of them.

57:11.333 --> 57:12.994
Let us enjoy the complexity.

57:13.254 --> 57:14.936
Let us pursue the complexity.

57:15.677 --> 57:21.822
This is why we can literally read your word every day and get something new out of every single day.

57:24.145 --> 57:29.049
Let us not pave it down to, well believe in Jesus, that's all you need.

57:29.570 --> 57:31.111
Well, that's part of it.

57:32.012 --> 57:35.856
If that were the case, it wouldn't be 66 books, it would be a pamphlet, a two page pamphlet.

57:37.057 --> 57:38.258
Jesus was born.

57:38.530 --> 57:40.212
He died, he rose again, there you go.

57:41.153 --> 57:57.753
That's part of it, but you don't even under, you can't appreciate that pamphlet until you step into the jungle of the Word of God and walk around the complexity of all that he has done and all that he is doing and all that he plans to do.

57:58.874 --> 58:02.418
We step into the complexity of your Word, maybe we step into the complexity of prayer,

58:03.586 --> 58:06.129
Supplications, yeah, that's part of it asking for things, sure.

58:06.389 --> 58:32.338
But maybe also include intercession, maybe also include worship, maybe also include thanksgiving, maybe also include the various components of what it means to sit with you in your presence, whether we're in the car, whether we're on the couch, or maybe embrace the complexity of our care groups and our various kinds of people.

58:33.474 --> 58:40.264
and actually thank you that we're not all the same, and thank you that we can learn from each other, and thank you that we can motivate and spur one another on.

58:41.867 --> 58:43.990
When I'm not motivated, somebody else is.

58:44.270 --> 58:45.953
When somebody's not motivated, I am.

58:47.495 --> 58:50.299
We see stuff that others don't see, and that's a good thing.

58:52.142 --> 58:57.410
Or maybe we embrace the complexity, not pay the, Lord, maybe we just embrace the process.

59:00.034 --> 59:02.578
Not be like Danita grabbing something.

59:02.754 --> 59:05.677
But maybe embrace the process of reading our Bible.

59:06.638 --> 59:09.321
It takes a long time to even get through the whole thing.

59:10.783 --> 59:11.804
And that's okay.

59:12.925 --> 59:15.468
This is a process, even to understand it.

59:18.211 --> 59:20.954
I've read through so many times, I still don't get half of it.

59:22.335 --> 59:23.376
It's a process.

59:23.657 --> 59:25.278
But, Lord, maybe embrace that process.

59:25.779 --> 59:27.721
I'm not trying to be scholars tomorrow.

59:28.001 --> 59:32.466
Maybe embrace the process of just being a child and being like, Father, what does this mean?

59:34.402 --> 59:35.063
What in the world?

59:35.964 --> 59:38.307
Why are you telling me about this today?

59:38.808 --> 59:39.569
Why today?

59:40.670 --> 59:41.371
I needed peace.

59:41.411 --> 59:42.953
Why are you talking to me about this?

59:43.974 --> 59:46.598
Maybe we embrace the process of prayer.

59:47.459 --> 59:48.180
We're not good at it.

59:48.200 --> 59:52.285
Nobody's good at prayer or no professional prayers.

59:53.667 --> 59:54.428
It's not a gift.

59:55.369 --> 59:56.330
It's not a fruit of the Spirit.

59:56.370 --> 59:57.372
It's not even a gift of the Spirit.

59:58.974 --> 59:59.695
It's a language.

59:59.715 --> 01:00:02.418
It's a jungle of the presence of God.

01:00:03.458 --> 01:00:08.283
May we embrace the process of whatever level we're at, whatever words we know, and however we feel.

01:00:08.644 --> 01:00:10.085
Or may we embrace the process.

01:00:12.268 --> 01:00:13.850
May we embrace the process of care groups.

01:00:16.953 --> 01:00:18.235
We can't attend every night.

01:00:18.335 --> 01:00:19.096
Okay, oh well.

01:00:20.677 --> 01:00:21.719
I can attend every other night.

01:00:21.999 --> 01:00:23.801
I can attend once a month.

01:00:23.861 --> 01:00:24.702
It's a process.

01:00:25.843 --> 01:00:26.884
It's not a product.

01:00:26.904 --> 01:00:29.287
You don't just jump to this perfect product.

01:00:30.549 --> 01:00:31.890
May we embrace the process.

01:00:32.738 --> 01:00:35.061
And honor the process.

01:00:35.322 --> 01:00:36.443
Value the process.

01:00:38.746 --> 01:00:40.228
And we embrace the process of this church.

01:00:41.150 --> 01:00:42.472
The city chapel is growing.

01:00:42.932 --> 01:00:43.813
We're not there yet.

01:00:45.396 --> 01:00:46.497
But we want more of you.

01:00:46.537 --> 01:00:48.921
We want to love people better.

01:00:50.483 --> 01:00:52.946
We want to display you more accurately.

01:00:52.986 --> 01:00:56.671
We want you to be even more glorified.

01:00:56.691 --> 01:00:58.514
We want more people to be baptized.

01:00:58.978 --> 01:01:07.168
in water and in fire and in the Holy Spirit, we want to go into all the world.

01:01:09.691 --> 01:01:10.712
We want to reach further.

01:01:12.414 --> 01:01:18.781
We have dreams and things we want to do more, but maybe embrace the process of where we're at right now.

01:01:19.983 --> 01:01:22.325
This is where we've been planted right now.

01:01:22.385 --> 01:01:23.547
This is who we have right now.

01:01:23.567 --> 01:01:24.768
This is what we can do right now.

01:01:24.788 --> 01:01:26.290
This is where we can go right now.

01:01:27.618 --> 01:01:30.642
And we value that and say, now there's value in where we are right now.

01:01:33.206 --> 01:01:34.367
It's awesome.

01:01:35.849 --> 01:01:38.493
It's awesome to be here, right here, right now.

01:01:38.933 --> 01:01:39.755
It's a privilege.

01:01:42.218 --> 01:01:45.843
Thank you, Lord, for letting us be in this process exactly where we're at.

01:01:47.285 --> 01:01:50.589
Letting us work through this process and walking with us.

01:01:51.611 --> 01:01:56.978
We'll give you all the praise and the glory and the honor for everything that you do, all the products that you produce,

01:01:57.538 --> 01:02:00.102
But in the meantime, we thank you for the process.

01:02:00.843 --> 01:02:01.964
In Jesus' name, we pray.

01:02:02.965 --> 01:02:03.286
Amen.

01:02:04.468 --> 01:02:04.808
Amen.

01:02:04.828 --> 01:02:06.210
Thank you guys for joining us today.

01:02:06.831 --> 01:02:07.672
